WEBVTT

00:01.697 --> 00:04.178
Amelia: What is the strongest
force in the world?

00:04.221 --> 00:06.919
If you were a layperson,
you might say gravity.

00:06.963 --> 00:09.052
♪

00:09.096 --> 00:10.706
If you were
a high school student,

00:10.749 --> 00:14.492
you might say electromagnetism.

00:14.536 --> 00:16.451
If you were a physicist,

00:16.494 --> 00:18.757
you might say nuclear.

00:18.801 --> 00:20.803
But you would all be wrong.

00:20.846 --> 00:23.719
Because the strongest force
in the world

00:23.762 --> 00:28.941
is the force of nature.

00:28.985 --> 00:31.422
♪

00:31.466 --> 00:33.076
Iris: No way.

00:33.120 --> 00:34.860
Your grandpa does
not listen to punk.

00:34.904 --> 00:36.645
I swear.
My grandma...

00:36.688 --> 00:38.908
Nature contains us all.

00:38.951 --> 00:40.823
We are nature.

00:40.866 --> 00:43.739
Cogs in a massive machine,
playing our part.

00:43.782 --> 00:45.784
...my grandpa would
just be like...

00:45.828 --> 00:48.091
[imitates electric guitar][Iris laughs]

00:48.135 --> 00:49.614
Playingmore than our part.

00:49.658 --> 00:52.182
We, as a race,
think we can escape

00:52.226 --> 00:55.055
its pronouncements,
skirt its rulings,

00:55.098 --> 00:57.318
sneak past its guards.

00:57.361 --> 01:00.147
It gives no consideration
to wants or needs,

01:00.190 --> 01:02.062
feelings or sentiment.

01:02.105 --> 01:03.889
We think we can steal from it

01:03.933 --> 01:07.110
and come away with its bounty
without consequence.

01:07.154 --> 01:08.894
But it contains us

01:08.938 --> 01:11.419
from our beginning to our end.

01:11.462 --> 01:17.686
♪

01:17.729 --> 01:21.559
The biological imperative that
all organisms must survive --

01:21.603 --> 01:25.520
to seek food, water,
shelter, to procreate --

01:25.563 --> 01:27.435
is the only reasonable offset

01:27.478 --> 01:31.178
to the crushing power
of nature.

01:31.221 --> 01:32.657
[Insects chittering]

01:40.143 --> 01:41.710
Iris: Huck says
the military

01:41.753 --> 01:43.581
blew all the bridges
over the Mississippi

01:43.625 --> 01:46.845
when things went back.

01:46.889 --> 01:50.284
Means
we'll need a boat.

01:50.327 --> 01:52.503
Huck: Crossing's
gonna be tough.

01:52.547 --> 01:54.462
And the terrain
on the other side,

01:54.505 --> 01:57.291
it's a lot rougher than
anything we've seen so far.

01:57.334 --> 02:00.729
You sure
you're ready to do this?

02:00.772 --> 02:02.383
[Deadpan] No.

02:02.426 --> 02:04.341
We really should...

02:04.385 --> 02:06.343
turn back.

02:06.387 --> 02:10.086
[Deadpan] Yeah, yeah.No, you've finally convinced us.

02:10.130 --> 02:11.783
Ha.

02:11.827 --> 02:15.047
[Both chuckle]

02:15.091 --> 02:16.658
[Chuckles]

02:16.701 --> 02:18.834
Felix: Hey, Elton, you wanna
give me a hand back here?

02:18.877 --> 02:21.010
I got these lines
all tangled up.

02:22.968 --> 02:24.883
Yeah. Sure.

02:37.069 --> 02:39.071
There is no tangle,
is there?

02:39.115 --> 02:42.118
Look, I think this is
the easiest route

02:42.162 --> 02:43.902
back around The Blaze.

02:46.427 --> 02:48.820
Huck and I...

02:48.864 --> 02:51.519
we're gonna bring it upto the others soon,

02:51.562 --> 02:54.261
once you help us
lay some groundwork

02:54.304 --> 02:57.307
and make the others seethat if we don't do this --

02:57.351 --> 02:58.830
Well, I ne-- I never --
I never said I was in.

02:58.874 --> 03:02.094
Yeah, but, you never saidthat you weren't.

03:06.925 --> 03:10.886
The Mississippi is
our last chance...

03:10.929 --> 03:13.715
for us to...
all get home safe.

03:13.758 --> 03:15.978
It just is.

03:16.021 --> 03:20.374
And I need youto help me get Silas

03:20.417 --> 03:23.115
and the girls to see that,
you understand?

03:23.159 --> 03:26.641
What makes you think
that they'd listen?

03:26.684 --> 03:29.774
Because they care
about you,

03:29.818 --> 03:33.517
just like you care
about them.

03:33.561 --> 03:37.260
That's gotta countfor something, right?

03:37.304 --> 03:46.661
♪

03:46.704 --> 03:49.577
Yet even with
our resolute will to survive,

03:49.620 --> 03:52.928
nature will end us,
because that is its law.

03:52.971 --> 03:54.799
[Camera shutter clicks] Death -- inevitable.

03:54.843 --> 03:56.279
[Growling weakly] Extinction --

03:56.323 --> 03:58.150
just another of its rules,

03:58.194 --> 04:01.153
another part of the life cycle
of the very old world

04:01.197 --> 04:02.851
churning with energy.[Thunder rumbling]

04:02.894 --> 04:05.419
There's no escape
from the inescapable.

04:05.462 --> 04:07.899
There is no respite
from the unceasing.

04:07.943 --> 04:10.380
It makes its choices for us.

04:10.424 --> 04:12.513
In short --

04:12.556 --> 04:14.428
accept the wind.

04:14.471 --> 04:16.995
It always wins.

04:17.039 --> 04:19.476
[Rumbling continues]

04:19.520 --> 04:21.826
♪

04:25.482 --> 04:32.663
♪

04:32.707 --> 04:33.925
Hope: Wow.

04:33.969 --> 04:36.363
So many options.

04:36.406 --> 04:39.148
I don't even know
where to start.

04:39.191 --> 04:47.287
♪

04:47.330 --> 04:49.767
Any updates?

04:49.811 --> 04:52.117
Elton's with us.

04:52.161 --> 04:53.684
Maybe.

04:53.728 --> 04:55.469
In a perfect world,
we'd have one more of them

04:55.512 --> 04:57.253
on our side, but...

04:57.297 --> 04:59.777
this is it.This is the only angle we got.

04:59.821 --> 05:02.345
I know.

05:02.389 --> 05:04.739
That's why I'm thinking ahead
to Plan B.

05:04.782 --> 05:08.090
♪

05:08.133 --> 05:10.875
Hell, maybe it doesn't
have to be all or nothing.

05:13.574 --> 05:15.358
What do you mean?

05:15.402 --> 05:18.753
I mean, if Corduroy gets
Silas to see the light,

05:18.796 --> 05:21.538
best way to keep 'em safe
might be if one of us

05:21.582 --> 05:23.323
keeps going
with the girls

05:23.366 --> 05:25.020
while the other
takes back the boys.

05:25.063 --> 05:26.282
Mm.

05:26.326 --> 05:27.457
[Both exhale sharply]

05:27.501 --> 05:28.980
Just puttin' it
out there.

05:29.024 --> 05:32.201
Yeah, well...[Sighs]

05:32.244 --> 05:33.898
Maybe we still got some time

05:33.942 --> 05:35.770
to change somehearts and minds, huh.

05:35.813 --> 05:38.163
♪

05:38.207 --> 05:39.208
[Sighs]

05:39.251 --> 05:44.256
♪

05:44.300 --> 05:46.041
Seems the locals used
these boats to evacuate

05:46.084 --> 05:47.477
when things
got hairy.

05:47.521 --> 05:51.351
It's likely we're looking
at the last of them.

05:51.394 --> 05:54.092
Then we'll get creative.

05:54.136 --> 05:56.704
Build our own.

05:56.747 --> 05:58.880
It's not exactly what I was
getting at with --

05:58.923 --> 06:00.229
Hope: Cool.

06:00.272 --> 06:01.839
Let's do it.

06:01.883 --> 06:04.059
Really?

06:04.102 --> 06:06.061
You're gonna
build a boat?

06:06.104 --> 06:09.499
Well...

06:09.543 --> 06:13.503
what if it's more of a...

06:13.547 --> 06:16.724
remodel?

06:16.767 --> 06:17.681
[Chuckles]

06:17.725 --> 06:19.466
Seems a bit precarious,

06:19.509 --> 06:21.293
don't you think?

06:21.337 --> 06:23.034
Silas: Could work.

06:23.078 --> 06:25.297
If we fix it up...

06:25.341 --> 06:27.038
add stuff.

06:27.082 --> 06:28.562
There was a warehousefurther north.

06:28.605 --> 06:32.348
See if there's stuffin there we can use.

06:32.392 --> 06:33.654
I say we hit it.

06:33.697 --> 06:42.532
♪

06:42.576 --> 06:43.707
[Scoffs]

06:43.751 --> 06:44.969
[Chuckles]

06:45.013 --> 06:46.580
[Banging on metal]

06:46.623 --> 06:49.974
♪

06:59.157 --> 07:01.159
Iris: [Sighs] This placelooks turned out.

07:01.203 --> 07:02.596
Hope: Maybe...

07:02.639 --> 07:04.554
maybe not.

07:22.529 --> 07:25.488
Uh, split up
and keep looking?

07:30.493 --> 07:33.017
[Clattering in distance]

07:42.810 --> 07:47.423
[Classical music plays]

07:47.467 --> 07:51.732
♪

07:51.775 --> 07:53.037
[Door opens]

07:53.081 --> 07:54.778
Amelia: Hi.Isaac: Hi.

07:54.822 --> 07:56.040
A lot of stuff.Yeah.

07:56.084 --> 07:59.783
Let's get some lights.[Chuckles]

07:59.827 --> 08:01.132
Oh, careful.

08:01.176 --> 08:05.136
It's very, very old.

08:05.180 --> 08:06.398
Even older than you?

08:06.442 --> 08:07.922
[Isaac and Amelia
exhale sharply]

08:07.965 --> 08:09.576
Older than pretty much
everything.

08:09.619 --> 08:16.452
♪

08:16.496 --> 08:18.062
One night
when I was 10,

08:18.106 --> 08:19.760
I was trying to take
a photo of Mars,

08:19.803 --> 08:26.070
and that fleeeeew
across the sky.

08:26.114 --> 08:29.639
Do you know what that is,
Elton?

08:29.683 --> 08:31.293
It's a meteor.

08:31.336 --> 08:34.557
It's a bunch of chunk of rock
flying through space

08:34.601 --> 08:36.646
at thousands of miles
an hour,

08:36.690 --> 08:39.562
faster than anything
you've seen.

08:39.606 --> 08:42.826
And when the meteor touches
the air around the earth,

08:42.870 --> 08:44.959
it starts to burn up,

08:45.002 --> 08:47.396
kind of like how when you rub
your hands together,

08:47.439 --> 08:50.530
they get hot.

08:50.573 --> 08:51.879
Like this?

08:51.922 --> 08:53.358
[Chuckles] Yeah.

08:53.402 --> 08:55.665
And sometimes,
the meteor makes it

08:55.709 --> 08:58.712
all the way
to the ground.

08:58.755 --> 09:00.322
Then what happens?

09:00.365 --> 09:03.455
That's what made all
the dinosaurs go away.

09:03.499 --> 09:05.980
This giant ball of fire
just c--
Isaac.

09:06.023 --> 09:08.896
Wh--
He's 5.

09:08.939 --> 09:11.768
If he wants to learn, Amelia,
he should learn.

09:11.812 --> 09:14.510
[Chuckles]It's never too early
for science, right?

09:14.554 --> 09:16.556
Elt-- Elton,
come here.

09:16.599 --> 09:18.601
You want to feel
something?

09:18.645 --> 09:20.255
Come here.
Come here.

09:20.298 --> 09:21.343
Wait.

09:21.386 --> 09:22.518
Right here?

09:22.562 --> 09:23.954
[Chuckles]Is that my little sister?

09:23.998 --> 09:27.088
Yeah! She's kicking.

09:27.131 --> 09:29.830
Oh, wait, I --
I think she's also saying,

09:29.873 --> 09:31.962
"I can't wait
to meet you."

09:32.006 --> 09:33.442
[Chuckles]

09:33.485 --> 09:34.878
If you're gonna teach him
about departures,

09:34.922 --> 09:36.184
I'm gonna teach him
about arrivals.

09:36.227 --> 09:37.838
It's only fair.[Cellphone vibrating]

09:37.881 --> 09:39.143
Oh.

09:42.233 --> 09:44.714
And my staff meeting at the U
just got moved up.

09:44.758 --> 09:46.020
[Sighs]
Oh.

09:46.063 --> 09:47.282
I have to go.

09:47.325 --> 09:48.239
[Whimpers]
I know.

09:48.283 --> 09:50.720
I'm sorry, baby.

09:50.764 --> 09:52.330
Be safe.
There's --

09:52.374 --> 09:53.984
Heard something's going onnear the hospital.

09:54.028 --> 09:55.464
There's a lot
of police activity.

09:55.507 --> 09:56.813
Okay.

09:59.294 --> 10:01.992
[Chuckles]

10:02.036 --> 10:06.040
I want to get another one likethat for my Esmerelda today.

10:06.083 --> 10:07.476
Who?

10:07.519 --> 10:08.956
My sister.

10:08.999 --> 10:10.958
That's what
I'm naming her.

10:11.001 --> 10:12.437
Oh.

10:12.481 --> 10:16.354
Okay, yeah, maybe...
we can talk about that.

10:16.398 --> 10:19.880
Well, a bracelet
is a very sweet gift, honey.

10:19.923 --> 10:23.013
I will [Sighs]
see you soon.

10:23.057 --> 10:24.058
Okay.

10:24.101 --> 10:26.713
I love you both.

10:26.756 --> 10:29.237
Bye.

10:29.280 --> 10:30.934
♪

10:30.978 --> 10:32.762
Alright.

10:32.806 --> 10:34.024
Come here, noodle.

10:34.068 --> 10:35.678
[Door opens]

10:35.722 --> 10:38.681
Let's [strains]
do some work.

10:38.725 --> 10:40.770
[Door closes]I'm gonna give you

10:40.814 --> 10:41.989
my favorite brush.

10:42.032 --> 10:42.990
Young Elton:
[Quietly] Thank you.

10:43.033 --> 10:43.947
Blow on it.

10:43.991 --> 10:44.905
[Blows]
Good.

10:44.948 --> 10:46.210
Blow on it.

10:46.254 --> 10:47.516
[Blows]
Ready?

10:47.559 --> 10:48.691
Yes.

10:48.735 --> 10:50.562
Go with the grain.

10:50.606 --> 10:52.216
[Police sirens wailing]That's --
That's the grain.

10:52.260 --> 10:54.523
Good, good.
Give it a little...

10:54.566 --> 10:56.133
Yeah.

10:56.177 --> 10:58.483
[Emergency signal blaring]You can't tell until --

10:58.527 --> 10:59.702
Ah-ha.

11:06.927 --> 11:09.843
Okay, we have barrels
for floatation,

11:09.886 --> 11:11.888
straps for binding,
fastening.

11:11.932 --> 11:13.977
Hope: A fan blade thatcould make a good propeller.

11:14.021 --> 11:16.719
And I spotted a shit-tonof pallets outside.

11:16.763 --> 11:19.983
Uh, got these, too.

11:20.027 --> 11:22.420
So, you're saying,
we're in business?

11:22.464 --> 11:24.727
Except we don't
have an engine.

11:24.771 --> 11:27.208
There's nothing
to fight the current.

11:27.251 --> 11:28.644
There's not much
left here,

11:28.688 --> 11:30.211
other than some
long-dead batteries,

11:30.254 --> 11:32.517
huge broken air conditioner,
a couple of bags of sand.

11:32.561 --> 11:34.476
W-- Uh, h-hold on.

11:34.519 --> 11:35.738
The A.C.

11:35.782 --> 11:37.261
I read about
how those work.

11:37.305 --> 11:40.656
We could use the partsand make some sort of, um...

11:40.700 --> 11:43.354
What's that called.
A steam boiler.

11:43.398 --> 11:45.313
It'd be like the still you madeback at the University.

11:45.356 --> 11:49.839
It's like the dorm furnaces
I had to fix.

11:49.883 --> 11:51.232
Hope: I guess.

11:51.275 --> 11:53.582
It's worth a shot, right?

11:53.625 --> 11:57.325
♪

11:57.368 --> 11:58.761
A'ight, then.

11:58.805 --> 12:00.284
Let's get to work.

12:00.328 --> 12:06.247
♪

12:09.729 --> 12:14.168
[Doc Robinson's "Meaning of
a Songbird Calling"plays]

12:14.211 --> 12:22.611
♪

12:22.654 --> 12:30.967
♪

12:31.011 --> 12:33.665
♪ Feel the sun come slowly

12:33.709 --> 12:36.320
♪ Makes the window glow

12:36.364 --> 12:37.800
Hey.

12:37.844 --> 12:41.543
Thanks.

12:41.586 --> 12:45.852
♪ All I need is
a place to dream ♪

12:45.895 --> 12:52.032
♪ And all I need is
clouds beneath my feet ♪

12:52.075 --> 12:58.865
♪

12:58.908 --> 13:05.741
♪

13:05.785 --> 13:08.526
[Hammers banging]

13:16.708 --> 13:18.885
[Chuckles] It's reallycoming together.

13:18.928 --> 13:20.190
Yeah.

13:20.234 --> 13:21.670
Looking great.

13:21.713 --> 13:23.063
It's funny.

13:23.106 --> 13:24.455
Working on this boat,

13:24.499 --> 13:27.850
it kinda makes it seemmore possible.

13:27.894 --> 13:31.158
Finding my dad.

13:31.201 --> 13:36.032
I mean, the river's probablythe last big thing in our way.

13:36.076 --> 13:38.208
[Chuckles] And once
we cross it...

13:40.471 --> 13:42.822
It's --
It's all downhill from here.

13:44.040 --> 13:45.650
Hey.

13:45.694 --> 13:47.174
[Quietly] Come here.

13:52.179 --> 13:54.790
Look, the closer we getto finishing this boat,

13:54.834 --> 13:56.444
the harder it's gonna beto sway the others,

13:56.487 --> 13:58.141
so...

13:58.185 --> 13:59.273
You wanna make
the pitch now?

13:59.316 --> 14:00.665
Yeah.

14:00.709 --> 14:02.015
Yeah, I think I shouldstart things off,

14:02.058 --> 14:04.539
then you an Elton come inwith the backup.

14:04.582 --> 14:08.717
[Hammering continues]Hey, I know you're just looking
out for 'em but...

14:08.760 --> 14:09.936
But...?

14:09.979 --> 14:12.416
Maybe it's time
to let this plan go.

14:12.460 --> 14:13.722
[Whispering] What areyou talking about

14:13.765 --> 14:15.593
"time to let
this plan go?"

14:15.637 --> 14:16.986
You know that this
is the only way

14:17.030 --> 14:19.597
that we get everyoneback safe.

14:19.641 --> 14:21.338
[Hammer thuds]

14:23.340 --> 14:25.081
Hey, is it true?

14:25.125 --> 14:26.604
You're working
behind our backs,

14:26.648 --> 14:28.302
trying to get us
to turn around?

14:28.345 --> 14:29.956
I --
Hold on, what --

14:29.999 --> 14:31.305
Iris: Hey.
What's going on?

14:31.348 --> 14:32.654
Him and Felix.

14:32.697 --> 14:34.351
They've been working
against us together,

14:34.395 --> 14:35.613
trying to make us
do a 180.

14:35.657 --> 14:37.877
No way.
He's committed to this.

14:37.920 --> 14:39.922
Iris: Hope, Elton is not
working with Felix --

14:39.966 --> 14:42.011
Yes, I am.
Sort of.

14:42.055 --> 14:44.535
Can we just talk
about this here?
Pass.

14:44.579 --> 14:46.233
You've been trying
to screw us over

14:46.276 --> 14:48.278
with Elton asyour little sidekick.

14:48.322 --> 14:49.801
What was your
Plan B, huh?

14:49.845 --> 14:51.412
Maybe sabotage the boatto make us to back?!

14:51.455 --> 14:54.241
No, of course not.

14:54.284 --> 14:56.243
Listen, h-h-he and Ihave been talking,

14:56.286 --> 14:59.289
and I agree witha lot of what he says, alright?

14:59.333 --> 15:02.466
It j-- m-makes sense.
You mean about going back?

15:02.510 --> 15:04.033
Seriously?

15:04.077 --> 15:05.382
What the hell happened
to seeing the world

15:05.426 --> 15:06.993
from start to finish?

15:07.036 --> 15:09.169
Listen to me.

15:09.212 --> 15:13.042
Yes, I was gonna have us
take the boat downriver,

15:13.086 --> 15:15.610
then head back up along
the banks of the Missouri

15:15.653 --> 15:18.047
until we reached
the University.

15:18.091 --> 15:19.788
It's safer than cutting
through The Blaze,

15:19.831 --> 15:21.877
and it's the smartest thing
for us right now.

15:21.921 --> 15:24.053
We don't know
where we're going.
[Scoffs]

15:24.097 --> 15:27.796
We don't know what we're gonna
do if an when we get there.

15:27.839 --> 15:30.494
We don't even know that
you're dad's really in trouble![Scoffs]

15:30.538 --> 15:32.975
Hell, for all we know,
he could've sent us 10 messages

15:33.019 --> 15:35.021
back at the University
right now from him

15:35.064 --> 15:36.979
telling us that
he's just fine!

15:37.023 --> 15:40.069
You don't even believe that.It doesn't matter
what I believe.

15:42.463 --> 15:45.031
He made me promise him
that I would keep you safe,

15:45.074 --> 15:47.729
and that is exactly
what I'm doing.You care more about a promisethan you do about his life?!

15:47.772 --> 15:49.687
Calm down, alright.
That is not what I'm saying!Iris: Stop! Stop!

15:49.731 --> 15:52.081
Yes, it is!We don't have time for this!

15:53.604 --> 15:56.172
There is still
so much left to do!

15:56.216 --> 15:59.436
And you know what,
leave your shit at the door.

15:59.480 --> 16:04.876
Because without each and every
one of us giving 100%...

16:04.920 --> 16:07.401
we're not making it
across that river.

16:07.444 --> 16:16.323
♪

16:16.366 --> 16:19.152
Huck: See anything
that could be fuel?

16:19.195 --> 16:24.026
Just driftwood, driftwood,and more driftwood.

16:24.070 --> 16:26.028
Better than nothin'.

16:26.072 --> 16:27.247
Let's grab it all.

16:27.290 --> 16:29.553
I can't believe
he would try

16:29.597 --> 16:31.381
and mess with Elton's headlike that.

16:31.425 --> 16:34.254
A-Actually, I can.

16:34.297 --> 16:35.733
They were only
trying to do

16:35.777 --> 16:37.822
what they felt was best
for everybody.

16:37.866 --> 16:40.216
Not something
you can fault them for.

16:40.260 --> 16:42.958
I can fault them
for being shady.

16:43.002 --> 16:46.657
You know what, I can fault themfor what you just said, too.

16:46.701 --> 16:49.486
Whatever.
They deserve it.

16:52.489 --> 16:55.188
So whose side
are you on?

16:55.231 --> 16:58.017
I heard what you said to himabout calling it off.

16:58.060 --> 17:00.323
Not gonna lie.

17:00.367 --> 17:02.586
For a while --

17:02.630 --> 17:05.067
a long while, yeah,

17:05.111 --> 17:09.071
I was all
for bringing you back.

17:09.115 --> 17:10.812
But now...

17:10.855 --> 17:13.119
I don't know.

17:13.162 --> 17:14.772
This thing we're doing
right now,

17:14.816 --> 17:18.341
going across country,
is big,

17:18.385 --> 17:20.213
maybe the biggest thing
we'll ever do.

17:20.256 --> 17:21.779
[Scoffs]

17:21.823 --> 17:23.738
It's shit like this
that makes us stronger...

17:23.781 --> 17:26.349
[Scoffs]
...makes us better.

17:34.662 --> 17:35.967
Okay.

17:39.362 --> 17:43.105
So everybody knows
how I got to the City.

17:43.149 --> 17:46.674
They found me floating down
the Missouri in a raft,

17:46.717 --> 17:49.198
arm broken,

17:49.242 --> 17:51.809
messed up,

17:51.853 --> 17:54.508
not sure if I was
coming or going.

17:54.551 --> 17:56.597
[Inhales deeply]

17:56.640 --> 17:59.252
Next thing I know,
they're calling me Huck.

17:59.295 --> 18:01.210
[Chuckles]

18:01.254 --> 18:03.212
Not that I mind.

18:03.256 --> 18:06.041
It's kinda cool, right?

18:06.085 --> 18:10.045
There's a lot I leave out
of that story.

18:10.089 --> 18:12.787
The days of not knowing
if I was gonna live or die.

18:12.830 --> 18:16.965
♪

18:17.008 --> 18:18.923
How close I came
to giving up.

18:22.666 --> 18:25.669
Letting the water
just take me away.

18:25.713 --> 18:28.759
♪

18:28.803 --> 18:30.239
Never woulda
lived long enough

18:30.283 --> 18:33.547
for Omaha security
to pick me up...

18:33.590 --> 18:36.289
if I didn't keep
pushing...

18:36.332 --> 18:38.595
every single moment.

18:41.424 --> 18:42.338
Shit.

18:42.382 --> 18:43.644
[Sniffles]

18:43.687 --> 18:45.515
I'm sorry.

18:45.559 --> 18:47.126
Nah.

18:47.169 --> 18:48.997
Don't be.

18:49.040 --> 18:50.041
[Exhales sharply]

18:50.085 --> 18:55.046
♪

18:55.090 --> 18:59.181
It pushes me
to overcome...

18:59.225 --> 19:00.835
to be stronger,

19:00.878 --> 19:02.576
better.

19:02.619 --> 19:05.666
Maybe that's whatthis whole thing is for you.

19:05.709 --> 19:08.843
The others, too.

19:08.886 --> 19:11.324
Even Felix.

19:11.367 --> 19:14.327
Maybe you should
tell him that.

19:14.370 --> 19:16.894
I was about to.

19:16.938 --> 19:19.636
Then Hurricane Hope struck.

19:19.680 --> 19:21.725
[Chuckles]

19:21.769 --> 19:23.379
And, um...

19:23.423 --> 19:25.729
maybe it's not my placeto tell him that.

19:28.036 --> 19:30.430
Maybe he's gotta figure it outfor himself.

19:30.473 --> 19:33.389
♪

19:33.433 --> 19:35.217
His own way.

19:35.261 --> 19:40.701
♪

19:42.659 --> 19:46.054
Let me get a word with her alonereal quick.

19:52.103 --> 19:54.976
[Sighs heavily]

19:55.019 --> 19:57.892
I know you're pissed off --I am.

19:57.935 --> 20:00.199
The thing is...

20:00.242 --> 20:02.418
I'm more pissed
at myself.

20:02.462 --> 20:04.681
Why's that?

20:04.725 --> 20:08.381
For being dumb enoughto think that we could turn you.

20:08.424 --> 20:12.298
That Icould turn you.

20:12.341 --> 20:14.256
My dad first took you in,

20:14.300 --> 20:16.432
I was so excited.

20:16.476 --> 20:18.217
Iris, too.

20:20.088 --> 20:21.524
We thought we weregonna get a brother,

20:21.568 --> 20:24.266
but we never got one becauseyou never acted like one.

20:24.310 --> 20:27.400
Dad gave you every chanceto be a real part of the family,

20:27.443 --> 20:28.879
and you never took it.

20:28.923 --> 20:31.926
We're not your sisters.We're your
problems.

20:35.059 --> 20:36.539
[Voice breaking]All you had to do was

20:36.583 --> 20:40.456
be the oneto tell him not to go.

20:40.500 --> 20:42.589
[Sniffles] He trusted you
more than anyone!

20:42.632 --> 20:43.938
He would've listened.Hope, I couldn't.

20:43.981 --> 20:47.115
You know what, no, it's cool!I get it.

20:47.158 --> 20:49.857
You had your reasons.

20:49.900 --> 20:52.163
But still, I-I hoped.

20:52.207 --> 20:54.165
You know?

20:54.209 --> 20:57.299
But joke's on me.

20:57.343 --> 20:59.736
You are who you are.

20:59.780 --> 21:03.827
Guess it's time
for me to grow up.

21:03.871 --> 21:07.831
♪

21:07.875 --> 21:09.311
[Fire whooshing]

21:09.355 --> 21:11.270
[Wood clattering]

21:13.359 --> 21:15.317
Fire's not hot enough.

21:15.361 --> 21:17.101
This shit ain't
cutting it.

21:17.145 --> 21:18.581
It's the best
we could find.

21:18.625 --> 21:20.409
Well, I don't know
what to tell you.

21:20.453 --> 21:22.324
Well,there has to be something.

21:24.761 --> 21:27.590
The nail polish box back
at the warehouse,

21:27.634 --> 21:30.724
it said
it was flammable.

21:30.767 --> 21:33.292
Alright.You and Elton take care of that.

21:33.335 --> 21:34.815
We'll finish up here.

21:34.858 --> 21:38.601
[Thunder crashes]

21:38.645 --> 21:40.386
Maybe double time it,huh?

21:40.429 --> 21:41.822
[Metal creaking]

21:41.865 --> 21:44.999
[Thunder rumbles]

21:45.042 --> 21:49.220
♪

21:54.051 --> 21:55.662
[Thunder rumbles]

21:55.705 --> 21:58.012
I don't like
the sound of that.

21:58.055 --> 22:00.319
We should grab
what we can fast.

22:00.362 --> 22:01.755
[Sighing] Yeah.

22:01.798 --> 22:02.843
Whoa.

22:02.886 --> 22:04.366
[Chuckles]

22:04.410 --> 22:06.281
Well, that doesn't quite
live up to its hype,

22:06.325 --> 22:07.587
now does it?

22:07.630 --> 22:09.153
Uh-uh.

22:11.417 --> 22:13.549
Wow.

22:13.593 --> 22:15.072
Nope.

22:19.990 --> 22:22.645
[Blows]

22:22.689 --> 22:23.951
[Metal thuds]

22:23.994 --> 22:25.692
So, this was
your plan?

22:28.999 --> 22:31.045
[Sighs]

22:31.088 --> 22:33.047
You really want
to get into this now?

22:36.093 --> 22:37.225
I'm not mad.

22:37.268 --> 22:38.531
Hmm.

22:38.574 --> 22:39.532
I'm just --

22:39.575 --> 22:41.229
Disappointed?

22:44.580 --> 22:47.627
[Grunts]

22:47.670 --> 22:50.369
Do you really think
my dad is safe?

22:50.412 --> 22:52.936
[Wind gusting]

22:52.980 --> 22:56.026
This rope's still
got some use in it.

22:56.070 --> 22:57.854
Felix.

23:01.902 --> 23:03.207
Yes.

23:06.428 --> 23:08.125
I think they're safe.

23:10.650 --> 23:12.434
Leo and Will.

23:14.958 --> 23:17.308
They haveto be safe.

23:17.352 --> 23:21.530
What do you mean?

23:21.574 --> 23:24.881
I was supposed to be the one
to go with your dad,

23:24.925 --> 23:25.969
alright?

23:26.013 --> 23:27.884
Not Will.

23:27.928 --> 23:32.454
Your dad asked me to stay behindand watch after you and Hope...

23:32.498 --> 23:34.325
and so Will took
my place.

23:40.070 --> 23:41.463
And that is why

23:41.507 --> 23:43.247
they have to be.

23:46.120 --> 23:48.862
I'm not there to protect them
if they aren't.

23:48.905 --> 23:51.430
I mean, I knew all that,but...

23:53.867 --> 23:57.523
I didn't knowhow you felt about it.

23:57.566 --> 23:59.786
Guess I didn't think
it mattered.

23:59.829 --> 24:03.703
What, b-being honest?

24:03.746 --> 24:05.487
That matters.

24:08.316 --> 24:11.667
When everything's
burning down,

24:11.711 --> 24:14.453
it is the only thingthat matters.

24:16.498 --> 24:19.240
[Thunder crashes]

24:19.283 --> 24:22.417
Well, we should go.

24:22.461 --> 24:24.027
Come on.

24:29.076 --> 24:31.992
[Walkers growling]

24:32.035 --> 24:34.516
[Rumbling continues]

24:36.997 --> 24:38.825
[Nail polish bottles clatter]

24:38.868 --> 24:41.480
[Nail polish dribbling]

24:44.395 --> 24:45.962
What?

24:46.006 --> 24:49.966
[Nail polish bottles clatter]

24:50.010 --> 24:53.274
I just don't want
anybody to die.

24:53.317 --> 24:55.581
And yes, I know
death is inevitable,

24:55.624 --> 24:57.539
but is it so horrible
to try to put it off

24:57.583 --> 24:59.323
for just
a little bit longer?

25:01.978 --> 25:04.677
The notion of fear is --
is biologically obsolete.

25:04.720 --> 25:07.549
It's just the body's
chemical reaction to risk,

25:07.593 --> 25:09.769
so if you can understand risk
on a conscious level,

25:09.812 --> 25:13.337
then there is no need
f-- for fear.

25:13.381 --> 25:17.777
[Distorted, distant screaming]

25:17.820 --> 25:19.518
[Screaming, banging]Okay.

25:19.561 --> 25:21.432
You have to listen to me,
okay, Elton?

25:21.476 --> 25:22.956
[Whimpers]I need you to stay
inside this box

25:22.999 --> 25:24.305
and be as quiet as you can,

25:24.348 --> 25:26.612
and you can't leave,
no matter what, okay?

25:26.655 --> 25:28.570
[Screaming, banging continue]Where are you going?

25:28.614 --> 25:30.529
I'm gonna go find us
a safe way home.

25:30.572 --> 25:32.008
And I'm gonna lock that door
from the outside

25:32.052 --> 25:33.488
so nothing can hurt you.

25:33.532 --> 25:34.881
Okay?

25:34.924 --> 25:36.709
And to be extra sure...

25:36.752 --> 25:40.843
[Screaming, banging]

25:40.887 --> 25:42.932
[Voice breaking]
This is a very special horn.

25:42.976 --> 25:44.368
Okay?

25:44.412 --> 25:46.849
It keeps anyone who's holding itsafe forever.

25:46.893 --> 25:48.416
So go ahead and hold it.

25:48.459 --> 25:49.765
Hold onto it tight, okay?

25:49.809 --> 25:50.984
[Crying][Police sirens wailing]

25:51.027 --> 25:52.768
I'm scared.

25:52.812 --> 25:54.596
[Banging in distance]

25:54.640 --> 25:56.555
Don't be.

25:56.598 --> 25:58.818
I'm not scared, okay?

25:58.861 --> 26:00.950
And you shouldn't be, either.[Gunshot, screaming]

26:00.994 --> 26:03.866
It's all gonna work out the way
it's supposed to, right?

26:03.910 --> 26:05.389
[Screaming continues]

26:05.433 --> 26:08.088
[Breathing heavily]
I love you, Elton.

26:08.131 --> 26:09.350
[Banging on doors]

26:09.393 --> 26:10.786
I love you, too.

26:10.830 --> 26:12.614
[Gunshots]

26:12.658 --> 26:15.356
[Crying]

26:15.399 --> 26:17.576
[Whispering]
It's okay.

26:17.619 --> 26:19.882
[Banging intensifies,
walkers growling]

26:21.884 --> 26:24.060
[Electricity buzzing]Weird.

26:24.104 --> 26:25.584
Is your skin
tingling?

26:25.627 --> 26:26.628
[Thunder rumbles]Get down!

26:26.672 --> 26:29.152
[Thunder crashes]

26:31.807 --> 26:35.332
Shit.
The hell did that
come from?

26:35.376 --> 26:37.552
[Walkers growling]

26:37.596 --> 26:39.859
[Rumbling continues]

26:39.902 --> 26:45.125
♪

26:45.168 --> 26:46.343
Felix...

26:46.387 --> 26:50.043
[Growling continues]

26:50.086 --> 26:53.046
Go, go, go,
go, go, go!

26:53.089 --> 26:55.918
[Growling continues]

26:59.182 --> 27:01.141
[Thunder rumbles]

27:01.184 --> 27:03.665
[Boiler puttering]

27:03.709 --> 27:05.885
It's getting closer.Hope: I know.

27:05.928 --> 27:07.582
Where the hellare Silas and Elton?

27:07.626 --> 27:08.801
[Loud clanking]

27:08.844 --> 27:10.541
Shit!

27:14.154 --> 27:16.286
[Walkers growling]

27:22.728 --> 27:25.208
[Liquid sloshing]

27:25.252 --> 27:27.167
♪

27:27.210 --> 27:29.604
That's a positive strike.

27:29.648 --> 27:31.388
Positive strikes
can happen

27:31.432 --> 27:32.999
20 miles awayfrom the storm's center.

27:33.042 --> 27:34.565
Judging by
the wind direction,

27:34.609 --> 27:36.306
we're minutes awayfrom being in the line of fire.

27:36.350 --> 27:39.266
Come on!

27:39.309 --> 27:41.790
♪

27:41.834 --> 27:43.792
Hey, there's a --

27:43.836 --> 27:46.316
Lightning storm headed
this way real fast.

27:46.360 --> 27:47.535
Yeah, we know.

27:47.578 --> 27:48.884
Iris: Empties, too.

27:48.928 --> 27:52.453
Couple dozen of them,maybe 15 minutes out.

27:52.496 --> 27:55.064
There's not enough time.
We need to take cover.

27:55.108 --> 27:56.587
The rising waterwill wash the boat away.

27:56.631 --> 27:57.937
We can't risk that.

27:57.980 --> 27:59.765
Okay, so we launch
before the shit hits.

27:59.808 --> 28:02.332
♪

28:02.376 --> 28:04.726
Where are Silas
and Elton?

28:04.770 --> 28:06.119
♪

28:06.162 --> 28:07.294
Whoa.

28:07.337 --> 28:13.735
♪

28:13.779 --> 28:16.912
I swear,that wasn't on purpose.

28:16.956 --> 28:22.352
♪

28:22.396 --> 28:24.006
Come on.

28:24.050 --> 28:25.878
[Grunts]

28:25.921 --> 28:30.534
♪

28:30.578 --> 28:31.971
Ow!Felix: What happened?

28:32.014 --> 28:33.450
Damn it!
You okay?

28:33.494 --> 28:34.974
I-I'm good.
I'm good.

28:35.017 --> 28:38.891
♪

28:38.934 --> 28:40.806
[Toolbox thuds]

28:40.849 --> 28:42.721
[Grunts]

28:42.764 --> 28:44.331
[Thunder crashes]

28:44.374 --> 28:45.593
♪

28:45.636 --> 28:46.637
Here they come.

28:50.511 --> 28:52.905
[Metal creaks]

28:52.948 --> 28:54.907
Thanks.

28:59.868 --> 29:01.957
[Boiler firing]

29:04.133 --> 29:06.222
-Yes.
-Alright.

29:10.879 --> 29:12.054
Whoa.

29:12.098 --> 29:13.752
[Metal groaning]No.

29:13.795 --> 29:17.233
[Boiler stops]

29:17.277 --> 29:19.540
[Steam hisses]

29:19.583 --> 29:21.498
♪

29:21.542 --> 29:22.804
Alright.
Add another problem.

29:22.848 --> 29:24.240
Elton, throw me
your fisherman.

29:24.284 --> 29:28.505
[Walkers growling]

29:28.549 --> 29:34.816
♪

29:34.860 --> 29:37.558
[Fishing reel whirs]

29:37.601 --> 29:38.689
[Growling continues]

29:38.733 --> 29:40.256
[Clanking]

29:40.300 --> 29:41.780
The drive belt's
come loose.

29:41.823 --> 29:43.346
Can we fix it?

29:43.390 --> 29:46.828
If somebody can fit down there
and reattach it...

29:46.872 --> 29:52.138
[Thunder rumbles]

29:52.181 --> 29:53.269
I can't.

29:53.313 --> 29:55.271
I-I-I'm claustrophobic.

29:55.315 --> 29:57.752
[Walkers growling]

29:57.796 --> 30:05.368
♪

30:05.412 --> 30:06.543
Elton.

30:06.587 --> 30:07.631
[Breathing heavily]

30:07.675 --> 30:11.505
[Distantly]
Elton, please.

30:11.548 --> 30:16.423
[Breathing shakily]

30:16.466 --> 30:24.779
♪

30:24.823 --> 30:26.868
You can do it, Elton.

30:26.912 --> 30:29.697
♪

30:29.740 --> 30:31.568
[Walkers growling]

30:31.612 --> 30:42.536
♪

30:42.579 --> 30:45.539
[Screaming and banging][Whispering shakily]
Mercury, Venus, Earth, Mars,

30:45.582 --> 30:48.716
Jupiter, Saturn,
Uranus, Neptune.

30:48.759 --> 30:50.674
Mercury, Venus, Earth, Mars,

30:50.718 --> 30:52.198
Jupiter, Saturn,
Uranus, Neptune.

30:52.241 --> 30:54.156
Mercury, Venus, Earth,
Mars, Jupiter...

30:54.200 --> 30:57.725
[Banging continues]Mercury, Venus, Earth, Mars...

30:57.768 --> 30:59.335
Mercury, Venus, Earth, Mars,

30:59.379 --> 31:01.207
Jupiter, Saturn,
Uranus, Neptune.

31:01.250 --> 31:04.732
Mercury, Venus, Earth,
Mars, Jupiter, Saturn!

31:04.775 --> 31:07.213
[Walkers growling]

31:07.256 --> 31:11.478
♪

31:11.521 --> 31:13.959
[Breathing heavily]

31:14.002 --> 31:17.788
♪

31:17.832 --> 31:19.878
[Grunts]

31:19.921 --> 31:21.749
[Metal clanking]

31:21.792 --> 31:23.098
♪

31:23.142 --> 31:26.754
[Walkers growling]

31:26.797 --> 31:34.675
♪

31:34.718 --> 31:36.546
O-Okay!

31:36.590 --> 31:39.767
[Boiler firing]

31:46.600 --> 31:48.907
[Screaming] I'm stuck!

31:48.950 --> 31:50.125
I'm stuck!

31:50.169 --> 31:51.257
Help!

31:51.300 --> 31:52.649
[Walkers growling]

31:52.693 --> 31:55.304
[Grunting]

31:55.348 --> 31:56.479
[Screams]

31:56.523 --> 32:01.354
♪

32:01.397 --> 32:03.008
[Growling continues]

32:03.051 --> 32:06.707
♪

32:06.750 --> 32:10.015
[Breathing heavily]

32:10.058 --> 32:15.672
♪

32:15.716 --> 32:19.024
This is
a very special horn.

32:19.067 --> 32:20.677
It keeps whomever's
holding it safe.

32:20.721 --> 32:26.553
[Banging, gunfire,
and police sirens continue]

32:26.596 --> 32:31.210
♪

32:31.253 --> 32:33.429
[Breathing heavily]

32:33.473 --> 32:35.040
You're alright.

32:35.083 --> 32:37.999
[Breathing heavily]

32:38.043 --> 32:39.218
You okay?

32:39.261 --> 32:41.698
I'm okay, I think.
Th-Th-Thank you.

32:41.742 --> 32:43.048
Thank you.

32:43.091 --> 32:44.832
Now we just gotta get this thingin the water.

32:44.875 --> 32:46.442
We don't have enough fuel
to keep the propeller running.

32:46.486 --> 32:48.096
Not to mention them.

32:48.140 --> 32:50.577
[Walkers growling]Let's move.

32:50.620 --> 32:52.666
♪

32:52.709 --> 32:54.102
Everybody ready?

32:54.146 --> 32:57.453
One three.
One, two, three.

32:57.497 --> 33:00.674
[All shouting, grunting]

33:00.717 --> 33:02.110
Come on!
We can do this!

33:02.154 --> 33:03.242
Again!

33:03.285 --> 33:06.201
One, two, three.

33:06.245 --> 33:09.900
[All shouting, grunting]

33:09.944 --> 33:12.338
♪

33:12.381 --> 33:14.601
No! No.
There's no time.

33:14.644 --> 33:15.994
We have to drop the boat
and make a run for it.

33:16.037 --> 33:17.212
The boat won't make it.

33:17.256 --> 33:19.127
Wewon't make it.Watch out.

33:19.171 --> 33:20.824
[Grunting] Come on.I can't do this by myself.

33:20.868 --> 33:22.609
Let's go.

33:22.652 --> 33:24.306
Come on, everyone.[All straining]

33:24.350 --> 33:25.307
Felix: Everybody, keep going.

33:25.351 --> 33:26.830
Come on.

33:26.874 --> 33:29.920
[Straining continues]

33:29.964 --> 33:36.057
♪

33:36.101 --> 33:38.146
-It's moving.
-It's moving. It's going.

33:38.190 --> 33:39.626
[Felix shouting]

33:39.669 --> 33:44.413
♪

33:44.457 --> 33:46.589
Come on!
It's almost there.

33:46.633 --> 33:48.461
[Walkers growling]

33:48.504 --> 33:51.986
-Go, go, go!
-Go!

33:52.030 --> 33:53.596
Aaaaaah!

33:53.640 --> 33:56.034
♪

33:56.077 --> 33:57.644
Get up! Come on.

33:57.687 --> 33:59.515
Come here!
Get up. Get up!

33:59.559 --> 34:01.256
[Walkers growling]

34:01.300 --> 34:09.221
♪

34:09.264 --> 34:11.092
Felix: You good?

34:11.136 --> 34:14.095
[Breathing heavily]

34:14.139 --> 34:16.054
-[Sighs] Hey.
-We did it.

34:16.097 --> 34:18.491
[Boiler puttering]

34:18.534 --> 34:27.500
♪

34:27.543 --> 34:30.024
[Growling continues]

34:30.068 --> 34:37.162
♪

34:37.205 --> 34:44.386
♪

34:47.824 --> 34:50.610
[Whispering
indistinctly]

34:50.653 --> 34:51.872
Why'd you do it?

34:51.915 --> 34:53.395
What?

34:53.439 --> 34:55.354
We would've
ditched the boat.

34:55.397 --> 34:58.400
I mean, that would've given you
more time to turn us around.

34:58.444 --> 35:01.142
Yeah, well,that woulda done zero good.

35:04.841 --> 35:07.279
And you and your sister...

35:07.322 --> 35:09.150
you really are
stubborn as shit.

35:09.194 --> 35:11.892
You know that, right?

35:11.935 --> 35:14.547
Look who's talking.

35:14.590 --> 35:16.592
Huck thinks
this'll be good for us.

35:16.636 --> 35:19.073
[Sighs]
That it'll turn us

35:19.117 --> 35:21.119
into the people
that we're supposed to be.

35:25.079 --> 35:26.515
We'll see.

35:29.388 --> 35:31.694
And for what
it's worth...

35:34.306 --> 35:37.004
...it was never
just about...

35:37.047 --> 35:38.701
a promise I made

35:38.745 --> 35:41.182
to your dad.

35:41.226 --> 35:42.705
I need you to know that.

35:44.620 --> 35:47.014
I do.

35:47.057 --> 35:51.061
For what it's worth,
leaving those clues behind

35:51.105 --> 35:54.543
wasn't just so you'd come
and turn us around.

35:54.587 --> 35:57.546
I was also hoping
that...

35:57.590 --> 35:58.982
Your here now,
alright.

35:59.026 --> 36:02.508
[Chuckles]
So, whatever.

36:02.551 --> 36:04.684
[Sighs]

36:07.165 --> 36:09.906
So, I take it
you're just --

36:09.950 --> 36:12.866
you're just good
with us moving forward?

36:12.909 --> 36:15.129
We'll keep 'em safe,

36:15.173 --> 36:19.264
and when we find Leo and Will,keep 'em safe, too.

36:19.307 --> 36:20.656
Yeah.

36:22.789 --> 36:23.790
But for now...

36:23.833 --> 36:25.444
Yeah.

36:25.487 --> 36:27.402
...I say we divide
and conquer.

36:30.100 --> 36:31.319
What do you mean?

36:34.235 --> 36:38.065
Huck: Hey, listen up.Everybody.

36:38.108 --> 36:41.808
I'm gonna spend the next dayor two scouting ahead.

36:41.851 --> 36:45.333
Our intel's weakfor this side of the river,

36:45.377 --> 36:47.509
and you're only as solid
as your intel.

36:47.553 --> 36:49.163
[Chuckles]
You're going off?

36:49.207 --> 36:50.599
On your own?

36:50.643 --> 36:54.255
Don't sweat it.I'll be back, 48 hours max.

36:54.299 --> 36:57.258
[Sighs]
Promise.

36:57.302 --> 37:00.653
Till then...you're in good hands.

37:00.696 --> 37:08.313
♪

37:08.356 --> 37:11.011
[Sighs deeply]

37:11.054 --> 37:14.667
♪

37:14.710 --> 37:16.321
[Fire crackles]

37:16.364 --> 37:19.976
♪

37:20.020 --> 37:22.762
[Insects chittering]

37:40.997 --> 37:42.738
[Sighs shakily]

37:45.263 --> 37:56.535
♪

37:56.578 --> 38:07.894
♪

38:07.937 --> 38:19.209
♪

38:19.253 --> 38:21.690
[Sobs softly]

38:21.734 --> 38:33.746
♪

38:33.789 --> 38:45.845
♪

38:45.888 --> 38:57.944
♪

38:57.987 --> 39:09.956
♪

39:09.999 --> 39:12.393
Elton: Here's the thing --

39:12.437 --> 39:16.223
Nature accounted for everything about the human race

39:16.266 --> 39:19.966
except our self awareness.

39:20.009 --> 39:23.448
Because we know we can change.[Gunfire, walkers growling]

39:23.491 --> 39:25.754
We can act in ways
nature wasn't expecting.

39:25.798 --> 39:27.234
Wasn't ready for.

39:27.277 --> 39:29.715
[Whimpering][Gunfire]

39:29.758 --> 39:31.194
[Gunfire stops]

39:31.238 --> 39:33.675
[Banging]

39:33.719 --> 39:35.547
[Radio chatter]

39:35.590 --> 39:36.809
Soldier: Clear!

39:36.852 --> 39:38.463
[Door bangs]

39:38.506 --> 39:40.987
♪

39:41.030 --> 39:43.729
So every now and again,

39:43.772 --> 39:46.558
that lets us see the path
through the wind,

39:46.601 --> 39:49.691
even if it's just for a moment.

39:49.735 --> 39:52.346
And sometimes...

39:52.390 --> 39:55.001
a moment is all you need.

39:55.044 --> 40:03.488
♪

40:03.531 --> 40:11.887
♪

40:11.931 --> 40:14.324
[Door creaks]

40:18.416 --> 40:20.418
[Electricity crackling]

40:20.461 --> 40:22.507
[Door creaks]

40:22.550 --> 40:25.118
[Crackling continues]

40:48.184 --> 40:49.795
[Sniffles]

40:54.408 --> 40:56.932
[Crackling continues]

41:08.074 --> 41:14.559
♪

41:14.602 --> 41:21.087
♪

41:21.130 --> 41:23.568
[Wind gusting]

41:23.611 --> 41:33.752
♪

41:33.795 --> 41:44.023
♪

41:44.066 --> 41:54.250
♪

41:54.294 --> 42:04.434
♪

42:04.478 --> 42:05.479
Hope: Hey.

42:05.523 --> 42:09.657
♪

42:09.701 --> 42:13.226
You okay?

42:13.269 --> 42:15.315
Yeah.

42:15.358 --> 42:17.143
[Clears throat]

42:17.186 --> 42:21.974
♪

42:22.017 --> 42:25.107
[Sighs shakily]

42:25.151 --> 42:27.806
The Night the Sky Fell...

42:27.849 --> 42:31.592
♪

42:31.636 --> 42:34.726
...my father told me
not to be scared.

42:34.769 --> 42:38.077
♪

42:38.120 --> 42:43.299
He said that he wasn't scared,and that I shouldn't be, either.

42:43.343 --> 42:46.607
♪

42:46.651 --> 42:49.567
But he was.

42:49.610 --> 42:51.481
[Sniffs]

42:51.525 --> 42:54.484
Probably more than he'd ever
been in his entire life.

42:56.530 --> 42:59.489
But...

42:59.533 --> 43:05.147
that didn't stop him from doing
what needed to be done.

43:07.759 --> 43:12.154
He was brave because
he was scared...

43:14.113 --> 43:16.332
not in spiteof it.

43:16.376 --> 43:20.249
♪

43:20.293 --> 43:23.339
I wish I could've
met your dad.

43:23.383 --> 43:26.429
And your mom.

43:26.473 --> 43:30.216
They must've been pretty coolto make a kid like you.

43:30.259 --> 43:34.176
♪

43:34.220 --> 43:36.483
[Scoffs] I-I know it's...

43:36.526 --> 43:39.094
crazy to even say,

43:39.138 --> 43:41.357
and [exhales sharply]

43:41.401 --> 43:45.405
the odds against it
are astronomical.

43:45.448 --> 43:57.417
♪

43:57.460 --> 43:58.897
[Voice breaking]
I sometimes think

43:58.940 --> 44:02.161
that she's still
out there...

44:02.204 --> 44:04.032
somewhere.

44:04.076 --> 44:11.736
♪

44:11.779 --> 44:15.565
With my sister,
Esmerelda.

44:15.609 --> 44:18.177
Both surviving

44:18.220 --> 44:20.048
together.

44:20.092 --> 44:23.965
♪

44:24.009 --> 44:27.099
That's not
so crazy to me.

44:27.142 --> 44:38.458
♪

44:38.501 --> 44:49.817
♪

44:49.861 --> 44:51.427
[Branch breaks]

44:51.471 --> 44:55.214
[Rustling]

44:55.257 --> 44:57.738
Iris: It's an empty.

45:02.917 --> 45:04.832
I can do it.

45:06.573 --> 45:08.793
Elton: Be right
behind you.

45:08.836 --> 45:11.578
I got this.

45:11.621 --> 45:18.106
♪

45:18.150 --> 45:24.634
♪

45:28.290 --> 45:37.996
♪

45:38.039 --> 45:47.788
♪

